RICIN - UK: (ENGLAND) SUSPECT CONVICTION
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 8 Mar 2010
Source: The Independent, Press Association report [edited]
<http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/white-supremacist-admits-producing-ricin-for-terrorism-1918210.html>



A white supremacist today [8 Mar 2010] admitted producing deadly
ricin while preparing for acts of terrorism.

The home of the alleged terrorist in Myrtle Grove, Burnopfield,
County Durham, was raided by anti-terror officers who found the
killer substance in a jam jar in his kitchen.

At Newcastle Crown Court he admitted producing a chemical weapon --
ricin -- and preparing for acts of terrorism. He also admitted to 3
charges of possessing a record containing information likely to be
useful to a person committing or preparing acts of terrorism.

The charge related to copies of 3 texts including The Anarchist's
Handbook, which detailed instructions on making explosives. This
probable terrorist, flanked by 4 prison officers, also admitted to
possession of a prohibited weapon, which related to a spray canister
found during the raid on his home.

He will be sentenced after the trial of his 19-year-old son, who
denies 2 charges of possessing material containing information likely
to be useful to a person committing or preparing acts of terrorism.
The case will be heard on [12 Apr 2010].

The father, a truck driver and ex-DJ, was remanded in custody and
Judge John Milford warned him: "Doubtless you have been told only
custody can follow."

The son was granted bail until his trial.

[Byline: Tom Wilkinson]

